I experienced something similar. The solution I found was the following:
```
const {errors} = useFormContext();
const error = get(errors, "name");
if(error && ('type' in error)) {
    // do something
}
```
The `get(...)` comes from [lodash](https://lodash.com/docs/4.17.15#get).

casting works, I did this: 
```
import { FieldError } from "react-hook-form";
{(errors[`${id}`]! as FieldError)!?.message}
```

can some one provide a codesandbox with this issue? I could get it not crying about type if i don't supply type for useForm or `any`

```
const { errors } = useForm<any>();
const { errors } = useForm();
```
